    <item>
      <title>George Benjamin, Pierre Boulez, Maurice Ravel</title>
      <link>https://walse.cz/opera/20250621-boulez-aimard-benjamin/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Jun 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://walse.cz/opera/20250621-boulez-aimard-benjamin/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;George Benjamin&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pierre-Laurent Aimard&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
  &lt;thead&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
          &lt;th style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;&lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/thead&gt;
  &lt;tbody&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Nikolai Obukhov&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Révélation&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Pierre Boulez&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Piano Sonata No. 1&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;George Benjamin&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Shadowlines for Piano&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Maurice Ravel&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Le Tombeau de Couperin for Piano&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;George Benjamin&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td style=&#34;text-align: left&#34;&gt;Divisions for Piano Four Hands&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;https://walse.cz/opera/20250621-boulez-aimard-benjamin/images/photo-1.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The final concert of the season dedicated to the 100th anniversary of Pierre Boulez’s birth features the revolutionary First Piano Sonata of 1946, one of the composer’s major early works. Pierre-Laurent Aimard, long considered to be among the most erudite performers of Boulez’s music, is joined by George Benjamin for this extraordinary program. Together, the two artists present the world premiere of Divisions, a new piece for piano four hands written by Benjamin specifically for the occasion. Aimard also performs Benjamin’s Shadowlines as well as works by Nikolai Obukhov and Maurice Ravel.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
